Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Cut @zucchini{1} lengthwise into four wedges, then slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick triangles. Quarter @roma tomatoes{4} lengthwise. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}.

Spread out zucchini, tomatoes, and scallion whites on a #baking sheet{}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%oz can}, then add to sheet. Sprinkle with a couple large drizzles of @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, and @chili flakes{1/4%tsp} (use less to taste). Roast in oven until zucchini is tender and tomatoes are soft and wilted, about ~{25%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Meanwhile, pick @basil{1/2%oz} leaves from stems. Reserve a few leaves for garnish and roughly chop the rest.

Carefully scoop out and reserve ¾ cup pasta cooking water. Drain penne, then return to pot and toss with a drizzle of olive oil.

Once veggies are done roasting, add to pot with pasta. Stir in chopped basil, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and @butter{2%tbsp}. Season generously with salt and pepper. Add just enough pasta cooking water to coat everything in a loose, creamy sauce—start with ½ cup and add more from there.

Divide pasta mixture between plates or bowls. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Break up @goat cheese{1%oz} into crumbles and sprinkle over top. Garnish with scallion greens and reserved basil leaves. Finish with a drizzle of olive oil and sprinkle with additional @?chili flakes{}, if desired.

> Goats are known for their tendency to buck and kick. Goat cheese, however, tastes best when you add a spicy kick. This pasta recipe with crumbles of the stuff weaves in a sprinkle of hot chili flakes to make it a little feisty. But there are roasted veggies and chickpeas, too, to ensure that every bite is filled with hearty, cozy wholesomeness.